trend_summary: The town remains largely wooded and low-rise, but each successive image shows pockets of new rooftops, bigger parking lots and added commercial sheds, especially on the north-east fringe and in the detached industrial park. Infill housing thickens along arterial roads, yet green corridors and the river buffer still dominate, limiting outward sprawl.
notable_changes: Expansion of industrial/commercial blocks at the north-east edge of the main city polygon.
Detached north-west park converts farmland into new warehouses and parking lots.
Incremental residential infill visible along central radials, shrinking open yards.
New parking areas and wider pavement around the downtown core.
Tree cover slightly reduced where small clearings appear for construction.
